<section id="overview">
  <div class="cge-container">
    <p class="cge-section-label fade-in">The Overview</p>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-in">AI built into the grid</h2>
    <p class="section-intro fade-in">
      Copilot in Excel is an AI assistant built directly into Excel. It understands plain-language requests, reads the data already in your workbook, and can analyze, explain, transform, build tables and formulas, generate charts and PivotTables, and act on multi-step instructions — while you stay in control. You preview a plan before anything changes, undo any action, and decide whether Copilot may edit your file or only talk to you about it.
    </p>

    <div class="callout callout-note fade-in" style="max-width:720px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
      <div class="callout-title">🛡️ Enterprise Data Protection</div>
      The <strong>shield icon</strong> in the Copilot pane means your session is protected. With a Microsoft 365 Copilot license, your prompts and workbook data stay within Microsoft's compliance boundary and are <strong>not used to train</strong> the foundation models.
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;" class="fade-in">Business outcomes you should expect</h3>
    <div class="comparison-wrapper fade-in">
      <table class="comparison-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Outcome</th><th>What it looks like in practice</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Time saved</td><td>Tasks that took 30–90 minutes (cleaning data, building a summary, writing a month-end narrative) drop to minutes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Higher quality</td><td>Consistent formatting, fewer formula errors, standardized structure across files and teams.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lower skill barrier</td><td>People who don't know PivotTables, XLOOKUP, or Power Query still get the result by describing it.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Faster decisions</td><td>Insights, outliers, and trends surface in seconds — meetings start from answers, not raw data.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Repeatability</td><td>Workbook Rules and Personalization make Copilot produce work your way, every time, without re-explaining.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;" class="fade-in">Where to find Copilot in Excel</h3>
    <div class="access-grid fade-in">
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">🎀</span><span>Home tab → <strong>Copilot</strong> button</span><span class="access-action">Ribbon</span></div>
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">✨</span><span>Floating sparkle on the grid</span><span class="access-action">In-canvas</span></div>
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">🧮</span><span>Type <strong>=COPILOT(</strong> in any cell</span><span class="access-action">Function</span></div>
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">🖱️</span><span>Right-click a selection</span><span class="access-action">Inline</span></div>
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">🌐</span><span>Excel for the web &amp; desktop</span><span class="access-action">Both</span></div>
      <div class="access-item"><span class="access-icon">🪪</span><span>"M365 Copilot (Premium)" in pane footer</span><span class="access-action">License</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-tip fade-in">
      <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip — don't confuse the add-ins</div>
      On the Home tab you may also see <strong>Excel Labs</strong> (a separate sandbox of experimental tools) and a third-party <strong>Finance</strong> add-in. Neither is Copilot. Copilot is the AI assistant button / floating sparkle.
    </div>

