  <div class="cge-container">
    <p class="cge-section-label fade-in">The Framework</p>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Prompt like a pro: G-C-O-F</h2>
    <p class="section-intro fade-in">The quality of what you get back is mostly determined by how you ask. Use this four-part structure for strong prompts.</p>

    <div class="gcse-grid fade-in">
      <div class="gcse-item"><div class="gcse-letter">G</div><div class="gcse-word">Goal</div><div class="gcse-desc">The outcome you want</div></div>
      <div class="gcse-item"><div class="gcse-letter">C</div><div class="gcse-word">Context</div><div class="gcse-desc">Which data / range / rules</div></div>
      <div class="gcse-item"><div class="gcse-letter">O</div><div class="gcse-word">Output</div><div class="gcse-desc">The format you expect</div></div>
      <div class="gcse-item"><div class="gcse-letter">F</div><div class="gcse-word">Format</div><div class="gcse-desc">Style, limits, must-dos</div></div>
    </div>

    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);max-width:760px;margin:0 auto 1.5rem;text-align:center;" class="fade-in">A complete prompt reads like this:</p>
    <div class="prompt-text fade-in" onclick="copyPrompt(this)" style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="highlight-goal">Build a monthly summary of sales by region</span> <span class="highlight-context">using the table on Sheet1 (columns A–F)</span> <span class="highlight-source">as a PivotTable with regions in rows and months in columns</span>, <span class="highlight-expectations">sorted by total descending, currency as $#,##0, with a totals row.</span><span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:1.25rem;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;" class="fade-in">Ten habits of effective Copilot users</h3>
    <div class="accordion fade-in">
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="accordion-icon">🎯</span><span class="accordion-title">Be specific &amp; iterate<span class="accordion-subtitle">point at a range, refine the draft</span></span>
          <svg class="accordion-chevron" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner">
          <p>Point Copilot at a named table or exact cells, not "my data." Ask for one outcome at a time when learning; chain steps once you trust it. Treat the first answer as a draft: <em>"Good — now group by quarter and add % change."</em></p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="accordion-icon">🧱</span><span class="accordion-title">State the output format<span class="accordion-subtitle">table, chart, PivotTable, narrative</span></span>
          <svg class="accordion-chevron" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner">
          <p>Tell Copilot exactly what you expect: a PivotTable, a bar chart, a 3-bullet narrative, a new column. Give an example of the shape: <em>"Format like this: Acme | $1,200 | 2026-06."</em></p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="accordion-icon">🚧</span><span class="accordion-title">Set guardrails<span class="accordion-subtitle">tell it what NOT to do</span></span>
          <svg class="accordion-chevron" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner">
          <p>Constraints sharpen results: <em>"Don't change column A; don't add new sheets; keep existing formulas."</em> Use <strong>Plan</strong> mode for anything important so you can review before changes land.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="accordion-icon">🧰</span><span class="accordion-title">Set it up once<span class="accordion-subtitle">Workbook Rules + Personalization</span></span>
          <svg class="accordion-chevron" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner">
          <p>Stop repeating standing preferences. Put formats, fiscal year, and naming in <strong>Workbook Rules</strong>; put tone and style in <strong>Personalization</strong>. Ask Copilot to <em>explain its work</em> so you can verify and learn.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="accordion-icon">✅</span><span class="accordion-title">Always verify<span class="accordion-subtitle">sanity-check before you share</span></span>
          <svg class="accordion-chevron" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner">
          <p>Check the numbers against a known total before you forward, publish, or decide. If results disappoint: add the missing context, break a big ask into two, switch to Plan mode to see the divergence, or try the newest model for complex/narrative tasks.</p>
        </div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:1.25rem;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;" class="fade-in">Prepare your data first</h3>
    <div class="callout callout-tip fade-in">
      <div class="callout-title">💡 Two minutes of prep = far better results</div>
      Convert your range to a <strong>Table (Ctrl+T)</strong> · use a <strong>single header row</strong> · keep one fact per cell · remove blank rows/columns inside the block · store numbers as numbers and dates as dates. Merged cells, stacked headers, and "numbers stored as text" are the top reasons Copilot gets it wrong.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

